0. Purpose
A unified engine that transforms raw state into multi-domain interpretations, ranked actions, and stored memory.
 
 
Pantheon is a system that ensures every important question is asked before action is taken.
 
This engine integrates:
• Language — semantic basis: how the state is described
• Mathematics — structural basis: how the state transforms
• Science — empirical basis: what the state can physically do
• 22 extended domains covering strategy, myth, cybernetics, memetics, and more
 
The engine is designed for use as the reasoning backbone of PantheonOS and as the execution layer for Inner Atlas, the embodied self-state tracker.
 
1. Core Principle
 
 
Reality is interpreted through multiple constraint systems. Power = selecting the right ones at the right time.
 
Three foundational statements govern all operation:
 
Languages choose how you SEE.
Mathematics chooses how things CAN CHANGE.
Science constrains what IS POSSIBLE.
 
Together they form the basis-switching principle: represent the same state in multiple coordinate systems, then select the minimum sufficient set to explain it and act on it.
More lenses is not better. Minimum sufficient lenses is the invariant.
 
