Routing Algorithm (Pseudocode)
function route(input: Signal): Domain[] {
 scores = {}
 for each domain d in ALL_DOMAINS:
   scores[d] = score(input, d.trigger_conditions)
 ranked = sort(scores, descending)
 cutoff = find_elbow(ranked)   // diminishing returns
 return ranked[:cutoff]        // minimum sufficient set
}
 
// Cutoff rule: stop adding domains when marginal
// explanatory gain < 0.15 of top domain score.
 
Override Policy
The auto-router recommendation is always overridable by the operator. Manual domain toggling takes precedence. Conductor records the override in the ledger for audit.
 
