8. Confidence Model
Level
Criteria
HIGH
≥ 2 domains at HIGH signal AND cross-domain agreement ≥ 0.7
MEDIUM
Mixed signal levels OR weak cross-domain agreement
LOW
Sparse data OR single high-signal domain, no corroboration
WEAK
Insufficient data to interpret. Flag and request more signal.
 
9. Memory Layer (EchoFrame)
EchoFrame is the temporal compression daemon. It converts execution outputs into distilled memory entries appended to the Mother Duck Ledger.
 
Compression Pipeline
• experience → raw snapshot stored
• patterns → delta from prior snapshot computed
• heuristics → recurring patterns flagged
• doctrine → stable patterns promoted to doctrine
• identity → doctrine integrated into StateVector
 
Memory Invariants
• Reversible compression — all memory must expand back without information loss
• Signal over noise — compress summaries, retain anomalies
• Retain failure cases — negative results are high-value signal
• Track recurrence — flag patterns that exceed frequency threshold
• Append-only — no deletion, only versioning and supersession
 
