11. Guardrails
 
These are architectural constraints, not preferences. All Pantheon operations must pass Mirror (ΣC ≥ 0.7) before execution.
 
Rule
Specification
No domain overrides reality
Interpretations are projections, not commands.
Myth is symbolic, not literal
Mythic output is resonance layer only. Never replaces empirical.
Compression must be reversible
Any compressed memory must expand back without information loss.
Minimum lens rule
Use the fewest domains that fully explain + permit action.
Separate signal/narrative
Always tag: signal (measured) vs. interpretation (inferred) vs. narrative (framed).
Mirror approval required
All actions pass Mirror gate: ΣC ≥ 0.7 before execution.
No autonomous irreversible acts
Spider executes; never takes irreversible real-world actions alone.
 
Separation Rule (Critical)
Every interpretation output must tag its category:
• Signal — measured, objective (e.g., pain intensity 7, sleep 4 hours)
• Interpretation — inferred from signal (e.g., recovery compromised)
• Narrative — symbolic framing (e.g., burden-bearing pattern)
Mirror rejects any output that conflates these categories.
 
